---
import AboutHeroImage from '@assets/blog-images/about/revised-about-hero-image.webp';
import Layout from '@layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import NikonF4Image from '@assets/nikon f4.png'
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="All about Aristocratic Arietta - Webdesigner, Seamstress, and more!"
	pubDate={new Date('2026-07-05T18:00:00-07:00')}
	updatedDate={new Date('2026-07-15T22:50:00-07:00')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<h2>Hi!</h2>
	<p>
		I'm Aristocratic Arietta, the webmaster of this very website! You can call me Arietta or Aria, just not Aristocratic because that's a mouthful! I am a college student who never got to experience the Y2K web, but I'm here to revist those times by making a website on Neocities!
	</p>
	<p>
		I have a lot of very different interests that I hope to share here. I am primarily a seamstress with a speciailty in Victorian dress, but I also dabble in 18<sup>th</sup> and 20<sup>th</sup> century dress as well. I have been sewing my entire life, and I hope to make it my career one day. I would love to work in costuming for film, theatre, and television. I do a lot of different crafts, my favorite being tatting (lace making). I hope to share some cool projects with you all!
	</p>
	<p>
		Outside of crafts, I love music! My music collection is quite large, as I collect vinyl records. I mostly collect new stuff, but I have some classics as well. I would share my Discogs account, but it is so incomplete it scares me. I am always listening to music when I am working or relaxing. When I am not near my record player, I am listening to music on Spotify. I am very specific in my tastes, but I am always looking for reccomendations.
	</p>
	<p>
		In other hobbies, I also love photography. Film photography, to be specific. I love the mystery of not knowing how the pictures will turn out! I shoot a healthy balance of black and white and color, all 35mm. I also have a small camera collection, but my go-to is my Nikon F4. It is a workhorse and I am obsessed with it. I want to get more lenses for it, though, as I only have two! I am far from the best photographer, but it really makes me happy to see improvement over time. Here's a picture of my behemoth F4 complete with flash, battery pack, and big 'ol lens:
	</p>
	<Image src={NikonF4Image} alt="My Nikon F4 camera with 70-210mm f/1.4 lens" class="camera-image"/>
	<p>
		I will be sharing a lot of the photos I take on here, so keep your eyes peeled for new photo dump posts! I just have to develop the like 6 rolls of film I have sitting in my fridge... I don't develop my own photos anymore, but I do scan them. That saves me money, as my local shop charges roughly $10/roll for just developing it. Occasionally, I make darkroom prints, but I haven't been very successful. I need to hear some tips and tricks from experienced darkroom artists, so if you think you have a few words of wisdom, let me know, and I will be forever indebted to you. ;)
	</p>
	<p>
		I am always looking for new friends, so if you made it this far go ahead and <a href="/fun-stuff/chat">say "Hi!" in my chat</a>, <a href="https://aristocraticarietta.atabook.org/">sign my guestbook,</a> or <a href="mailto:aristocraticarietta@proton.me">send me an email!</a> (I love receiving emails, by the way!) Any of those options would be much appreciated! No need to get fancy or write paragraphs, just reach out and say "Hi!" I always follow back (provided you have a NeoCities site ;). Toodles!
	</p>
